<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,906,1795]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1662,1687]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is composed of the Latin words 
<emphasis box="[813,854,1663,1686]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">tres</emphasis>
, three, and 
<emphasis box="[983,1043,1663,1686]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">spina</emphasis>
, thorn, referring to the three strong spine-like setae on the male sternite IV.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
